article.headline: VMI 73, Liberty 67
article.story: LEXINGTON, Va. (AP) -- Reggie Williams scored 13 points and Tim Allmond and Tadas Mankevicius each added 12 to lead VMI to a 73-67 win over Liberty Thursday night. The Keydets (8-16, 2-11 Big South Conference) took the lead for good on a 3-pointer by Sean Christiansen with 3:33 left in the first. Liberty closed the gap to one twice in the next three minutes, but trailed 30-27 at the half. The Flames got no closer than three points in the second half. Brian Woodson scored 26 points and nabbed 9 turnovers for the Flames (11-14, 9-5). Larry Blair added 18 points and Leo Lightbourne had 12 rebounds.
